oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: U.S.S. Nashville, Key West Harbor, Fla., U.S.A.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Launched in 1895, the Nashville was the only gunboat of its class. Along with firing the first shot in the Spanish-American War, it also captured four Spanish vessels and assisted in cutting the Atlantic telegraph cable between Cuba and Spain. Here it is in Key West, Florida in 1898.
Keel laid in 1894; 220 ft. long; 38 ft. 3 in. breadth; 11 t. draft; 14 knots top speed.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Gunboats; Warships; Ships
